<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,540,1069]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,411,540,565]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Conical-depressed shell; rather low spire; roundly trapezoidal aperture; narrow and deep umbilicus bordered by a row of pointed knobs; spiral rows of granules; sharp peripheral keel; strong spiral cord encircling the umbilicus. Protoconch: heterostrophic; about 2 whorls; first whorl deeply immersed, last whorl bulging from the top of the spire; diameter about 770 µm; surface smooth; transition to the teleoconch marked by a thin, everted lip.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,540,1069]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,719,744]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Remarks</emphasis>
. It is of note that the original spelling 
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" box="[761,829,719,744]" class="Gastropoda" family="Architectonicidae" genus="Solarium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="allerii">
<emphasis box="[761,829,719,744]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">allerii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was modified in 1878 by Monterosato, and the new spelling 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale, 1931" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1931" box="[246,319,756,781]" class="Gastropoda" family="Architectonicidae" genus="Solatisonax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alleryi">
<emphasis box="[246,319,756,781]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">alleryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been exclusively used for this taxon afterwards (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bieler" box="[950,1174,756,781]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refString="Bieler, R. &amp; Petit, R. E. (2005) Catalogue of Recent and fossil taxa of the family Architectonicidae Gray, 1850 (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Zootaxa, 1101, 1 - 119." type="journal article" year="2005">Bieler &amp; Petit 2005</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,540,1069]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,791,816]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC11 (
<specimenCount box="[659,791,791,816]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
), BC67 (4), BC71 (7), BC72 (7); cores BC04 (2), BC21 (1), BC51 (5), BC67 (2), BC72 (6). Maximum diameter: 
<quantity box="[791,859,828,852]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1436,540,1069]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,502,863,888]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Iredale, 1931" authorityName="Iredale" authorityYear="1931" box="[521,737,863,888]" class="Gastropoda" family="Architectonicidae" genus="Solatisonax" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Heterostropha" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="alleryi">
<emphasis box="[521,737,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Solatisonax alleryi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ranges from the eastern Atlantic (including seamounts) to eastern Mediterranean, dwelling on mud at circalittoral to bathyal depths (Melone &amp; Taviani 1984; 
<bibRefCitation author="Beck" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refString="Beck, T., Metzger, T. &amp; Freiwald, A. (2006) BIAS-Biodiversity inventorial atlas of macrobenthic seamount animals. OASIS Deliverable 25, Final Report, 124 pp." type="book" year="2006">
Beck 
<emphasis box="[1377,1436,900,925]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
). The Indopacific specimens reported by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bieler" box="[709,865,935,960]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" refString="Bieler, R. (1993) Architectonicidae of the Indo-Pacific (Mollusca, Gastropoda). Abhandlungen des Naturwissenschaftlichen Vereins in Hamburg, N. F., 30, 1 - 377." type="journal article" year="1993">Bieler (1993)</bibRefCitation>
come from mud, sand and stones of the lower sublittoral zone (
<quantity box="[339,471,972,996]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.04" metricValueMax="4.3" metricValueMin="1.78" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" unit="m" value="304.0" valueMax="430.0" valueMin="178.0">178–430 m</quantity>
).
</paragraph>
